# Backend API base URL — read via process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL
# (Expo inlines any EXPO_PUBLIC_* var at build time, no extra config needed).
#
# - iOS Simulator: http://localhost:3001 works as-is (the Simulator shares
#   your Mac's network stack).
# - Physical device via Expo Go: "localhost" means the phone itself, not
#   your Mac — use your Mac's LAN IP instead, e.g. http://192.168.1.23:3001.
#   Find it with `ipconfig getifaddr en0` on macOS.
# - Android emulator: use http://10.0.2.2:3001 instead of localhost.
#
# Copy this file to .env and adjust if the default (localhost, Simulator)
# doesn't fit your setup.
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3001
